rComments: Very fair exams and clear expectations. She made a hard class easier to do well in and really cares that her students actually learn the material. She's also energetic during lectures which is important for anatomy classes. I would take her class again in a heartbeat.

She talks and moves through slide really fast. Didn't bother showing up after the second class. Really nice lady tho and she acc cares about her students success. Solid prof but u gotta know ur stuff for her exams

Anatomy is a tough subject made easy by Dr Elbeshbeishys lectures and slides. She is very knowledgeable as I found out she has a PhD in Anatomy. She answers emails promptly and is very compassionate towards her students. Definitely recommend her course.
My QUEEN! Such a good anatomy prof and really cares about her students. Easy exams and really informative lectures. Take her class if you have the chance!

She's a really sweet lady, but not a great prof. The class is all memorization with TONS of diagrams. Other profs for the same course made it clear what to study but she never did, leaving us to try to memorize every muscle, bone, joint, etc. in the entire body. Go to class because she puts blanks in the slides that can be hard to find in the book.
It was her first year teaching this course, but she was always available and provided many great resources. She really cares for students and wants everyone to succeed.

She is a fast talker and moves from one slide to the next quite fast. She is, however, very caring and wants everyone to do good. Expects people to read ahead before class and again after class to make it easier to grasp to all the new material. Tries to bell curve to make sure the class average stays high.
